Skill plans
Year 8 science
IXL offers more than 100 year 8 science skills to explore and learn! Not sure where to start? Go to your personalised Recommendations wall to find skills picked just for you, or select a skill plan that aligns to your textbook, territory curriculum or standardised test.

A.	Science practices and tools
1	The process of scientific inquiry (6)
2	Identify laboratory tools (2)
3	Laboratory safety equipment (4)
B.	Designing experiments
1	Identify control and experimental groups (9)
2	Identify independent and dependent variables (9)
3	Identify the experimental question (9)
4	Identify questions that can be investigated with a set of materials (7)
5	Understand an experimental protocol about plant growth (13)
6	Understand an experimental protocol about diffusion (13)
7	Understand an experimental protocol about evaporation (13)
C.	Engineering practices
1	Identify parts of the engineering-design process (4)
2	Evaluate tests of engineering-design solutions (15)
3	Use data from tests to compare engineering-design solutions (11)
4	Explore the engineering-design process: going to the Moon! (5)
D.	Density
1	Calculate density, mass and volume (4)
E.	Atoms and molecules
1	What are atoms and chemical elements? (10)
2	How are substances represented by chemical formulas and models? (7)
3	Identify chemical formulas for ball-and-stick models (6)
4	Describe the atomic composition of molecules (5)
5	Classify elementary substances and compounds using chemical formulas (4)
6	Classify elementary substances and compounds using models (4)
F.	Chemical reactions
1	Identify reactants and products (10)
2	Count atoms and molecules in chemical reactions (7)
3	Calculate amounts of reactants or products in chemical reactions (17)
4	Describe energy changes in chemical reactions (15)
5	Compare physical and chemical changes (6)
6	Explore chemical structure and properties: soap-making (10)
7	Explore chemical structure and properties: food flavours (8)
8	Synthetic materials (8)
G.	Force and motion
1	Identify whether objects are accelerating (8)
2	How does mass affect force and acceleration? (10)
3	Predict forces using Newton's third law (11)
4	Balanced and unbalanced forces (15)
H.	Kinetic and potential energy
1	Identify changes in gravitational potential energy (7)
2	Use tables and graphs to identify patterns about kinetic energy (19)
3	Explore energy transformations: roller coaster ride (11)
4	Explore energy transformations: bike ride (11)
 
I.	Electricity and magnetism
1	Electric forces and fields (7)
2	Compare magnitudes of magnetic forces (8)
J.	Thermal energy
1	Predict heat flow and temperature changes (9)
2	Compare thermal energy transfers (7)
K.	Particle motion and energy
1	How does particle motion affect temperature? (11)
2	Particle motion and changes of state (13)
3	How does particle motion affect gas pressure? (9)
4	Identify how particle motion affects temperature and pressure (9)
L.	Waves
1	Transverse waves (9)
2	Longitudinal waves (8)
3	Transmission, reflection and absorption of waves (9)
4	Electromagnetic waves (10)
5	Applications of infrared waves (9)
6	Effects of ultraviolet waves (8)
M.	Solutions
1	Compare concentrations of solutions (2)
2	Diffusion across membranes (7)
N.	Classification and scientific names
1	Identify common and scientific names (9)
2	Origins of scientific names (4)
3	Use scientific names to classify organisms (6)
O.	Biochemistry
1	The chemistry of cellular respiration (7)
P.	Cells
1	Understanding cells (10)
2	Identify functions of plant cell parts (2)
3	Identify functions of animal cell parts (3)
4	Plant cell diagrams: label parts (6)
5	Animal cell diagrams: label parts (6)
6	Compare cells and cell parts (10)
7	Mitosis and the cell cycle (3)
Q.	Anatomy and physiology
1	Organisation in the human body (8)
2	Body systems: circulation and respiration (5)
3	Body systems: digestion (5)
4	Body systems: removing waste (7)
5	Body systems: perception and motion (5)
6	Science literacy: how does the nervous system produce phantom pain? (6)
R.	Fossils
1	Compare ages of fossils in a rock sequence (9)
S.	Plant reproduction
1	Angiosperm and conifer life cycles (3)
2	Moss and fern life cycles (3)
T.	Photosynthesis
1	How do plants use and change energy? (13)
2	Identify the photosynthetic organism (10)
 
U.	Ecosystems
1	Describe populations, communities and ecosystems (8)
2	Identify ecosystems (5)
3	Describe ecosystems (5)
V.	Ecological interactions
1	How does matter move in food chains? (4)
2	Interpret food webs I (4)
3	Interpret food webs II (10)
4	Use food chains to predict changes in populations (9)
5	Classify symbiotic relationships (7)
6	Investigate primary succession on a volcanic island (6)
W.	Conservation
1	Coral reef biodiversity and human uses: explore a problem (9)
2	Coral reef biodiversity and human uses: evaluate solutions (5)
X.	Natural resources and human impacts
1	Evaluate claims about natural resource use: fossil fuels (8)
Y.	Rocks
1	Introduction to the rock cycle (11)
2	Classify rocks as igneous, sedimentary or metamorphic (5)
3	Label parts of rock cycle diagrams (14)
4	Select parts of rock cycle diagrams (3)
Z.	Earth's features
1	Label Earth layers (9)
2	Label Earth features at tectonic plate boundaries (9)
3	Describe tectonic plate boundaries around the world (6)
AA.	The water cycle
1	Label parts of water cycle diagrams (9)
2	Select parts of water cycle diagrams (2)
BB.	The atmosphere
1	Explore air masses (13)
2	Identify and compare air masses (11)
3	How do air masses form? (8)
CC.	Weather and climate
1	Use data to describe climates (9)
2	Factors affecting climate: latitude (9)
3	Factors affecting climate: altitude (9)
4	Factors affecting climate: distance from the ocean (8)
DD.	Astronomy
1	Analyse models of the Earth-Sun-Moon system (13)
2	Identify phases of the Moon (8)
3	Solar eclipses (8)
4	Lunar eclipses (10)
5	What causes the seasons on Earth? (7)
6	Analyse data to compare properties of planets (10)
7	Identify constellations (3)
EE.	Units and measurement
1	Choose units of distance, mass and volume (7)
2	Abbreviate time, length, speed and acceleration units (4)
3	Abbreviate mass and volume units (6)
4	Abbreviate force, energy and electricity units (4)
